 Content Security Policy (CSP) Header Not Set
Description
Content Security Policy (CSP) is an added layer of security that helps to detect and mitigate certain types of attacks, including Cross Site Scripting (XSS) and data injection attacks. These attacks are used for everything from data theft to site defacement or distribution of malware. CSP provides a set of standard HTTP headers that allow website owners to declare approved sources of content that browsers should be allowed to load on that page â€” covered types are JavaScript, CSS, HTML frames, fonts, images and embeddable objects such as Java applets, ActiveX, audio and video files.

<h1>Optimize your rhythms <br>and stay healthy</h1>
<p>A new type of app that helps you understand your<br> body's rhythms while contributing to research.</p>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec text-center">
<div class="container">
<h2>What are Circadian Rhythms?</h2>
<p>Circadian rhythms are the daily timetables that are present in every cell of every organ in our body, including the brain. Circadian rhythms are the master program that instructs at what time of the day or night every brain chemical, every hormone, every enzyme rises and/or fall. These daily rhythms enable our brain and body to achieve their optimum performance at every hour of the day or night and allow our body to carry out its daily repair and rejuvenation. When we have broken circadian rhythms, the risk for many diseases including obesity, diabetes, heart disease, fatty liver disease, gut diseases, and cancer goes up. By nurturing our rhythms we can prevent, manage, and even reverse many of these diseases.</p>
</div>
</section>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec text-center">
<div class="container">
<h2>How to nurture your rhythms?</h2>
<p>When we eat, sleep and exercise shapes our rhythms. By timing these daily habits to the right time of our daily lives, we can have healthy rhythms. In this research study, we want to know how your daily habits of eating, sleeping and exercising affects your health, Based on that, we will guide you to optimize these habits which in turn will optimize your rhythms so you can lead a long, healthy life.</p>
</div>
</section>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec cnt_with_side_img rt_img">
<div class="container">
<div class="row">
<div class="col-md-6">
<article>
<h2>Track everything you
eat and drink </h2>
<p>Food, beverages, and medications can influence your body&rsquo;s circadian rhythms. Use the mCC app to log everything that you eat or drink to help us understand how the timing of food, beverages, and medication influences your circadian rhythms.</p>
</article>
</div>
<div class="col-md-6">
<figure>
<img src="https://stag.mycircadianclock.andolasoft.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/landing-food-1.png" alt="">
</figure>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec cnt_with_side_img lft_img">
<div class="container">
<div class="row lft_img_second_child">
<div class="col-md-6">
<figure>
<img src="https://stag.mycircadianclock.andolasoft.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/landing-steps.png" alt="">
</figure>
</div>
<div class="col-md-6">
<article>
<h2>Track your Exercise and Steps</h2>
<p>Use the mCC app to log your exercise and sync the mCC app with Google Fit or Apple Health to capture your daily step counts.
</p>
</article>
</div>

</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec much_more_sec">
<div class="container">
<div class="row">
<div class="col-md-6">
<figure>
<img src="https://stag.mycircadianclock.andolasoft.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/much-more.png" alt="">
</figure>
</div>
<div class="col-md-6">
<article>
<h2 class="much_more_ttl">And much more&hellip;</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<strong>Medicine Reminder</strong>
<p>Timing of medicines and supplements matters. By sharing what medication and when you take them will help us gain better insight into optimal timing for meds and supplements. Along the way, set reminders so that you don&rsquo;t miss your supplements and meds.</p>
</li>
<li>
<strong>Water Reminder</strong>
<p>Hydration is an energy booster. If you often forget to hydrate enough, use the app to track your intake and stay hydrated.</p>
</li>
<li>
<strong>Health Log</strong>
<p>You can help our research on how the timing of food, sleep and exercise affects your health by periodically sharing your health measurements. They include body weight, blood pressure, blood glucose and a few more.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</article>
</div>
</div>

<h1>Optimize your rhythms <br>and stay healthy</h1>
<p>A new type of app that helps you understand your<br> body's rhythms while contributing to research.</p>

</figure>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec text-center">
<div class="container">
<h2>What are Circadian Rhythms?</h2>
<p>Circadian rhythms are the daily timetables that are present in every cell of every organ in our body, including the brain. Circadian rhythms are the master program that instructs at what time of the day or night every brain chemical, every hormone, every enzyme rises and/or fall. These daily rhythms enable our brain and body to achieve their optimum performance at every hour of the day or night and allow our body to carry out its daily repair and rejuvenation. When we have broken circadian rhythms, the risk for many diseases including obesity, diabetes, heart disease, fatty liver disease, gut diseases, and cancer goes up. By nurturing our rhythms we can prevent, manage, and even reverse many of these diseases.</p>
</div>
</section>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec text-center">
<div class="container">
<h2>How to nurture your rhythms?</h2>
<p>When we eat, sleep and exercise shapes our rhythms. By timing these daily habits to the right time of our daily lives, we can have healthy rhythms. In this research study, we want to know how your daily habits of eating, sleeping and exercising affects your health, Based on that, we will guide you to optimize these habits which in turn will optimize your rhythms so you can lead a long, healthy life.</p>
</div>
</section>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec cnt_with_side_img rt_img">
<div class="container">
<div class="row">
<div class="col-md-6">
<article>
<h2>Track everything you
eat and drink </h2>
<p>Food, beverages, and medications can influence your body&rsquo;s circadian rhythms. Use the mCC app to log everything that you eat or drink to help us understand how the timing of food, beverages, and medication influences your circadian rhythms.</p>
</article>
</div>
<div class="col-md-6">
<figure>
<img src="https://stag.mycircadianclock.andolasoft.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/landing-food-1.png" alt="">
</figure>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec cnt_with_side_img lft_img">
<div class="container">
<div class="row lft_img_second_child">
<div class="col-md-6">
<figure>
<img src="https://stag.mycircadianclock.andolasoft.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/landing-steps.png" alt="">
</figure>
</div>
<div class="col-md-6">
<article>
<h2>Track your Exercise and Steps</h2>
<p>Use the mCC app to log your exercise and sync the mCC app with Google Fit or Apple Health to capture your daily step counts.
</p>
</article>
</div>

</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec cnt_with_side_img rt_img">
<div class="container">

<p>Use the mCC app to log your sleep time and quality.</p>

</article>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec much_more_sec">
<div class="container">
<div class="row">
<div class="col-md-6">
<figure>
<img src="https://stag.mycircadianclock.andolasoft.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/much-more.png" alt="">
</figure>
</div>
<div class="col-md-6">
<article>
<h2 class="much_more_ttl">And much more&hellip;</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<strong>Medicine Reminder</strong>
<p>Timing of medicines and supplements matters. By sharing what medication and when you take them will help us gain better insight into optimal timing for meds and supplements. Along the way, set reminders so that you don&rsquo;t miss your supplements and meds.</p>
</li>
<li>
<strong>Water Reminder</strong>
<p>Hydration is an energy booster. If you often forget to hydrate enough, use the app to track your intake and stay hydrated.</p>
</li>
<li>
<strong>Health Log</strong>
<p>You can help our research on how the timing of food, sleep and exercise affects your health by periodically sharing your health measurements. They include body weight, blood pressure, blood glucose and a few more.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</article>
</div>

function setCurrentTheme( theme ) {
var pictures = document.getElementsByClassName( 'neve-site-logo' );
for(var i = 0; i<pictures.length; i++) {
var picture = pictures.item(i);
if( ! picture ) {
continue;
};
var fileExt = picture.src.slice((Math.max(0, picture.src.lastIndexOf(".")) || Infinity) + 1);
if ( fileExt === 'svg' ) {
picture.removeAttribute('width');
picture.removeAttribute('height');
picture.style = 'width: var(--maxwidth)';
}
var compId = picture.getAttribute('data-variant');
if ( compId && variants[compId] ) {
var isConditional = variants[compId]['same'];
if ( theme === 'light' || isConditional || variants[compId]['dark']['src'] === false ) {
picture.src = variants[compId]['light']['src'];
picture.srcset = variants[compId]['light']['srcset'] || '';
picture.sizes = variants[compId]['light']['sizes'];
continue;
};
picture.src = variants[compId]['dark']['src'];
picture.srcset = variants[compId]['dark']['srcset'] || '';
picture.sizes = variants[compId]['dark']['sizes'];
};
};
};
var observer = new MutationObserver(function(mutations) {
mutations.forEach(function(mutation) {
if (mutation.type == 'attributes') {
theme = html.getAttribute('data-neve-theme');
setCurrentTheme(theme);
};
});
});
observer.observe(html, {
attributes: true
});

Instances 1
Solution
Modern Web browsers support the Content-Security-Policy and X-Frame-Options HTTP headers. Ensure one of them is set on all web pages returned by your site/app.

If you expect the page to be framed only by pages on your server (e.g. it's part of a FRAMESET) then you'll want to use SAMEORIGIN, otherwise if you never expect the page to be framed, you should use DENY. Alternatively consider implementing Content Security Policy's "frame-ancestors" directive.
Reference https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/X-Frame-Options

<h1>Optimize your rhythms <br>and stay healthy</h1>
<p>A new type of app that helps you understand your<br> body's rhythms while contributing to research.</p>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec text-center">
<div class="container">
<h2>What are Circadian Rhythms?</h2>
<p>Circadian rhythms are the daily timetables that are present in every cell of every organ in our body, including the brain. Circadian rhythms are the master program that instructs at what time of the day or night every brain chemical, every hormone, every enzyme rises and/or fall. These daily rhythms enable our brain and body to achieve their optimum performance at every hour of the day or night and allow our body to carry out its daily repair and rejuvenation. When we have broken circadian rhythms, the risk for many diseases including obesity, diabetes, heart disease, fatty liver disease, gut diseases, and cancer goes up. By nurturing our rhythms we can prevent, manage, and even reverse many of these diseases.</p>
</div>
</section>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec text-center">
<div class="container">
<h2>How to nurture your rhythms?</h2>
<p>When we eat, sleep and exercise shapes our rhythms. By timing these daily habits to the right time of our daily lives, we can have healthy rhythms. In this research study, we want to know how your daily habits of eating, sleeping and exercising affects your health, Based on that, we will guide you to optimize these habits which in turn will optimize your rhythms so you can lead a long, healthy life.</p>
</div>
</section>

eat and drink </h2>
<p>Food, beverages, and medications can influence your body&rsquo;s circadian rhythms. Use the mCC app to log everything that you eat or drink to help us understand how the timing of food, beverages, and medication influences your circadian rhythms.</p>

<h2 class="much_more_ttl">And much more&hellip;</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<strong>Medicine Reminder</strong>
<p>Timing of medicines and supplements matters. By sharing what medication and when you take them will help us gain better insight into optimal timing for meds and supplements. Along the way, set reminders so that you don&rsquo;t miss your supplements and meds.</p>
</li>
<li>
<strong>Water Reminder</strong>
<p>Hydration is an energy booster. If you often forget to hydrate enough, use the app to track your intake and stay hydrated.</p>
</li>
<li>
<strong>Health Log</strong>
<p>You can help our research on how the timing of food, sleep and exercise affects your health by periodically sharing your health measurements. They include body weight, blood pressure, blood glucose and a few more.</p>
</li>
</ul>

<h1>Optimize your rhythms <br>and stay healthy</h1>
<p>A new type of app that helps you understand your<br> body's rhythms while contributing to research.</p>

<img width="125" height="37" src="https://stag.mycircadianclock.andolasoft.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Tedx.png" class="img-fluid wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" />

</figure>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec text-center">
<div class="container">
<h2>What are Circadian Rhythms?</h2>
<p>Circadian rhythms are the daily timetables that are present in every cell of every organ in our body, including the brain. Circadian rhythms are the master program that instructs at what time of the day or night every brain chemical, every hormone, every enzyme rises and/or fall. These daily rhythms enable our brain and body to achieve their optimum performance at every hour of the day or night and allow our body to carry out its daily repair and rejuvenation. When we have broken circadian rhythms, the risk for many diseases including obesity, diabetes, heart disease, fatty liver disease, gut diseases, and cancer goes up. By nurturing our rhythms we can prevent, manage, and even reverse many of these diseases.</p>
</div>
</section>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec text-center">
<div class="container">
<h2>How to nurture your rhythms?</h2>
<p>When we eat, sleep and exercise shapes our rhythms. By timing these daily habits to the right time of our daily lives, we can have healthy rhythms. In this research study, we want to know how your daily habits of eating, sleeping and exercising affects your health, Based on that, we will guide you to optimize these habits which in turn will optimize your rhythms so you can lead a long, healthy life.</p>
</div>
</section>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec cnt_with_side_img rt_img">
<div class="container">
<div class="row">
<div class="col-md-6">
<article>
<h2>Track everything you
eat and drink </h2>
<p>Food, beverages, and medications can influence your body&rsquo;s circadian rhythms. Use the mCC app to log everything that you eat or drink to help us understand how the timing of food, beverages, and medication influences your circadian rhythms.</p>
</article>
</div>
<div class="col-md-6">
<figure>
<img src="https://stag.mycircadianclock.andolasoft.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/landing-food-1.png" alt="">
</figure>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec cnt_with_side_img lft_img">
<div class="container">
<div class="row lft_img_second_child">
<div class="col-md-6">
<figure>
<img src="https://stag.mycircadianclock.andolasoft.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/landing-steps.png" alt="">
</figure>
</div>
<div class="col-md-6">
<article>
<h2>Track your Exercise and Steps</h2>
<p>Use the mCC app to log your exercise and sync the mCC app with Google Fit or Apple Health to capture your daily step counts.
</p>
</article>
</div>

</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec cnt_with_side_img rt_img">
<div class="container">

<h2>Track your Sleep </h2>
<p>Use the mCC app to log your sleep time and quality.</p>

</article>
</div>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec much_more_sec">
<div class="container">
<div class="row">
<div class="col-md-6">
<figure>
<img src="https://stag.mycircadianclock.andolasoft.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/much-more.png" alt="">
</figure>
</div>
<div class="col-md-6">
<article>
<h2 class="much_more_ttl">And much more&hellip;</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<strong>Medicine Reminder</strong>
<p>Timing of medicines and supplements matters. By sharing what medication and when you take them will help us gain better insight into optimal timing for meds and supplements. Along the way, set reminders so that you don&rsquo;t miss your supplements and meds.</p>
</li>
<li>
<strong>Water Reminder</strong>
<p>Hydration is an energy booster. If you often forget to hydrate enough, use the app to track your intake and stay hydrated.</p>
</li>
<li>
<strong>Health Log</strong>
<p>You can help our research on how the timing of food, sleep and exercise affects your health by periodically sharing your health measurements. They include body weight, blood pressure, blood glucose and a few more.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</article>
</div>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec text-center">
<div class="container">
<h2>What are Circadian Rhythms?</h2>
<p>Circadian rhythms are the daily timetables that are present in every cell of every organ in our body, including the brain. Circadian rhythms are the master program that instructs at what time of the day or night every brain chemical, every hormone, every enzyme rises and/or fall. These daily rhythms enable our brain and body to achieve their optimum performance at every hour of the day or night and allow our body to carry out its daily repair and rejuvenation. When we have broken circadian rhythms, the risk for many diseases including obesity, diabetes, heart disease, fatty liver disease, gut diseases, and cancer goes up. By nurturing our rhythms we can prevent, manage, and even reverse many of these diseases.</p>
</div>
</section>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec text-center">
<div class="container">
<h2>How to nurture your rhythms?</h2>
<p>When we eat, sleep and exercise shapes our rhythms. By timing these daily habits to the right time of our daily lives, we can have healthy rhythms. In this research study, we want to know how your daily habits of eating, sleeping and exercising affects your health, Based on that, we will guide you to optimize these habits which in turn will optimize your rhythms so you can lead a long, healthy life.</p>
</div>
</section>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec cnt_with_side_img rt_img">

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec text-center">
<div class="container">
<h2>What are Circadian Rhythms?</h2>
<p>Circadian rhythms are the daily timetables that are present in every cell of every organ in our body, including the brain. Circadian rhythms are the master program that instructs at what time of the day or night every brain chemical, every hormone, every enzyme rises and/or fall. These daily rhythms enable our brain and body to achieve their optimum performance at every hour of the day or night and allow our body to carry out its daily repair and rejuvenation. When we have broken circadian rhythms, the risk for many diseases including obesity, diabetes, heart disease, fatty liver disease, gut diseases, and cancer goes up. By nurturing our rhythms we can prevent, manage, and even reverse many of these diseases.</p>
</div>
</section>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec text-center">
<div class="container">
<h2>How to nurture your rhythms?</h2>
<p>When we eat, sleep and exercise shapes our rhythms. By timing these daily habits to the right time of our daily lives, we can have healthy rhythms. In this research study, we want to know how your daily habits of eating, sleeping and exercising affects your health, Based on that, we will guide you to optimize these habits which in turn will optimize your rhythms so you can lead a long, healthy life.</p>
</div>
</section>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec cnt_with_side_img rt_img">
<div class="container">
<div class="row">
<div class="col-md-6">
<article>
<h2>Track everything you
eat and drink </h2>
<p>Food, beverages, and medications can influence your body&rsquo;s circadian rhythms. Use the mCC app to log everything that you eat or drink to help us understand how the timing of food, beverages, and medication influences your circadian rhythms.</p>
</article>
</div>
<div class="col-md-6">
<figure>
<img src="https://stag.mycircadianclock.andolasoft.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/landing-food-1.png" alt="">
</figure>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec cnt_with_side_img lft_img">
<div class="container">
<div class="row lft_img_second_child">

<figure>
<img src="https://stag.mycircadianclock.andolasoft.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/landing-steps.png" alt="">
</figure>
</div>
<div class="col-md-6">
<article>
<h2>Track your Exercise and Steps</h2>
<p>Use the mCC app to log your exercise and sync the mCC app with Google Fit or Apple Health to capture your daily step counts.
</p>
</article>
</div>

</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec much_more_sec">
<div class="container">
<div class="row">
<div class="col-md-6">
<figure>
<img src="https://stag.mycircadianclock.andolasoft.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/much-more.png" alt="">
</figure>
</div>
<div class="col-md-6">
<article>
<h2 class="much_more_ttl">And much more&hellip;</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<strong>Medicine Reminder</strong>
<p>Timing of medicines and supplements matters. By sharing what medication and when you take them will help us gain better insight into optimal timing for meds and supplements. Along the way, set reminders so that you don&rsquo;t miss your supplements and meds.</p>
</li>
<li>
<strong>Water Reminder</strong>
<p>Hydration is an energy booster. If you often forget to hydrate enough, use the app to track your intake and stay hydrated.</p>
</li>
<li>
<strong>Health Log</strong>
<p>You can help our research on how the timing of food, sleep and exercise affects your health by periodically sharing your health measurements. They include body weight, blood pressure, blood glucose and a few more.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</article>
</div>

var html = document.documentElement;

var variants = {"logo":{"light":{"src":"https:\/\/stag.mycircadianclock.andolasoft.co.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/MCC-logo-white.svg","srcset":false,"sizes":""},"dark":{"src":"https:\/\/stag.mycircadianclock.andolasoft.co.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/MCC-logo-white.svg","srcset":false,"sizes":""},"same":true}};
function setCurrentTheme( theme ) {
var pictures = document.getElementsByClassName( 'neve-site-logo' );
for(var i = 0; i<pictures.length; i++) {
var picture = pictures.item(i);
if( ! picture ) {
continue;
};
var fileExt = picture.src.slice((Math.max(0, picture.src.lastIndexOf(".")) || Infinity) + 1);
if ( fileExt === 'svg' ) {
picture.removeAttribute('width');
picture.removeAttribute('height');
picture.style = 'width: var(--maxwidth)';
}
var compId = picture.getAttribute('data-variant');
if ( compId && variants[compId] ) {
var isConditional = variants[compId]['same'];
if ( theme === 'light' || isConditional || variants[compId]['dark']['src'] === false ) {
picture.src = variants[compId]['light']['src'];
picture.srcset = variants[compId]['light']['srcset'] || '';
picture.sizes = variants[compId]['light']['sizes'];
continue;
};
picture.src = variants[compId]['dark']['src'];
picture.srcset = variants[compId]['dark']['srcset'] || '';
picture.sizes = variants[compId]['dark']['sizes'];
};
};
};
var observer = new MutationObserver(function(mutations) {
mutations.forEach(function(mutation) {
if (mutation.type == 'attributes') {
theme = html.getAttribute('data-neve-theme');
setCurrentTheme(theme);
};
});
});
observer.observe(html, {
attributes: true
});
/* ]]> */

The page must not contain any content that is transmitted over unencrypted HTTP.

This includes content from third party sites.

<h1>Optimize your rhythms <br>and stay healthy</h1>
<p>A new type of app that helps you understand your<br> body's rhythms while contributing to research.</p>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec text-center">
<div class="container">
<h2>What are Circadian Rhythms?</h2>
<p>Circadian rhythms are the daily timetables that are present in every cell of every organ in our body, including the brain. Circadian rhythms are the master program that instructs at what time of the day or night every brain chemical, every hormone, every enzyme rises and/or fall. These daily rhythms enable our brain and body to achieve their optimum performance at every hour of the day or night and allow our body to carry out its daily repair and rejuvenation. When we have broken circadian rhythms, the risk for many diseases including obesity, diabetes, heart disease, fatty liver disease, gut diseases, and cancer goes up. By nurturing our rhythms we can prevent, manage, and even reverse many of these diseases.</p>
</div>
</section>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec text-center">
<div class="container">
<h2>How to nurture your rhythms?</h2>
<p>When we eat, sleep and exercise shapes our rhythms. By timing these daily habits to the right time of our daily lives, we can have healthy rhythms. In this research study, we want to know how your daily habits of eating, sleeping and exercising affects your health, Based on that, we will guide you to optimize these habits which in turn will optimize your rhythms so you can lead a long, healthy life.</p>
</div>
</section>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec cnt_with_side_img rt_img">

eat and drink </h2>

<h2 class="much_more_ttl">And much more&hellip;</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<strong>Medicine Reminder</strong>
<p>Timing of medicines and supplements matters. By sharing what medication and when you take them will help us gain better insight into optimal timing for meds and supplements. Along the way, set reminders so that you don&rsquo;t miss your supplements and meds.</p>

Solution
Ensure that your web server, application server, load balancer, etc. is configured to suppress the "Server" header or provide generic details.

Description
HTTP Strict Transport Security (HSTS) is a web security policy mechanism whereby a web server declares that complying user agents (such as a web browser) are to interact with it using only secure HTTPS connections (i.e. HTTP layered over TLS/SSL). HSTS is an IETF standards track protocol and is specified in RFC 6797.

<h1>Optimize your rhythms <br>and stay healthy</h1>
<p>A new type of app that helps you understand your<br> body's rhythms while contributing to research.</p>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec text-center">
<div class="container">
<h2>What are Circadian Rhythms?</h2>
<p>Circadian rhythms are the daily timetables that are present in every cell of every organ in our body, including the brain. Circadian rhythms are the master program that instructs at what time of the day or night every brain chemical, every hormone, every enzyme rises and/or fall. These daily rhythms enable our brain and body to achieve their optimum performance at every hour of the day or night and allow our body to carry out its daily repair and rejuvenation. When we have broken circadian rhythms, the risk for many diseases including obesity, diabetes, heart disease, fatty liver disease, gut diseases, and cancer goes up. By nurturing our rhythms we can prevent, manage, and even reverse many of these diseases.</p>
</div>
</section>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec text-center">
<div class="container">
<h2>How to nurture your rhythms?</h2>
<p>When we eat, sleep and exercise shapes our rhythms. By timing these daily habits to the right time of our daily lives, we can have healthy rhythms. In this research study, we want to know how your daily habits of eating, sleeping and exercising affects your health, Based on that, we will guide you to optimize these habits which in turn will optimize your rhythms so you can lead a long, healthy life.</p>
</div>
</section>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec cnt_with_side_img rt_img">
<div class="container">
<div class="row">
<div class="col-md-6">
<article>
<h2>Track everything you
eat and drink </h2>
<p>Food, beverages, and medications can influence your body&rsquo;s circadian rhythms. Use the mCC app to log everything that you eat or drink to help us understand how the timing of food, beverages, and medication influences your circadian rhythms.</p>
</article>
</div>
<div class="col-md-6">
<figure>
<img src="https://stag.mycircadianclock.andolasoft.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/landing-food-1.png" alt="">
</figure>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec cnt_with_side_img lft_img">
<div class="container">
<div class="row lft_img_second_child">
<div class="col-md-6">
<figure>
<img src="https://stag.mycircadianclock.andolasoft.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/landing-steps.png" alt="">
</figure>
</div>
<div class="col-md-6">
<article>
<h2>Track your Exercise and Steps</h2>
<p>Use the mCC app to log your exercise and sync the mCC app with Google Fit or Apple Health to capture your daily step counts.
</p>
</article>
</div>

</div>
</div>
</section>

</div>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec much_more_sec">
<div class="container">
<div class="row">
<div class="col-md-6">
<figure>
<img src="https://stag.mycircadianclock.andolasoft.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/much-more.png" alt="">
</figure>
</div>
<div class="col-md-6">
<article>
<h2 class="much_more_ttl">And much more&hellip;</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<strong>Medicine Reminder</strong>
<p>Timing of medicines and supplements matters. By sharing what medication and when you take them will help us gain better insight into optimal timing for meds and supplements. Along the way, set reminders so that you don&rsquo;t miss your supplements and meds.</p>
</li>
<li>
<strong>Water Reminder</strong>
<p>Hydration is an energy booster. If you often forget to hydrate enough, use the app to track your intake and stay hydrated.</p>
</li>
<li>
<strong>Health Log</strong>
<p>You can help our research on how the timing of food, sleep and exercise affects your health by periodically sharing your health measurements. They include body weight, blood pressure, blood glucose and a few more.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</article>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</section>

Instances 3
Solution
Ensure that your web server, application server, load balancer, etc. is configured to enforce Strict-Transport-Security.
Reference https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/HTTP_Strict_Transport_Security_Cheat_Sheet.html
https://owasp.org/www-community/Security_Headers
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HTTP_Strict_Transport_Security
https://caniuse.com/stricttransportsecurity
https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc6797
Tags OWASP_2021_A05
OWASP_2017_A06
CWE-319
CWE Id 319
WASC Id 15
Plugin Id 10035
Low
 Timestamp Disclosure - Unix
Description
A timestamp was disclosed by the application/web server. - Unix
URL https://stag.mycircadianclock.andolasoft.co.in/
Method GET
Parameter
Attack
Evidence 1726643238
Other Info 1726643238, which evaluates to: 2024-09-18 12:37:18.
Show / hide Request and Response
Request Header - size: 700 bytes.
GET https://stag.mycircadianclock.andolasoft.co.in/ HTTP/1.1
host: stag.mycircadianclock.andolasoft.co.in
Connection: keep-alive
sec-ch-ua: "Chromium";v="128", "Not;A=Brand";v="24", "Google Chrome";v="128"
sec-ch-ua-mobile: ?0
sec-ch-ua-platform: "Windows"
Upgrade-Insecure-Requests: 1

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec text-center">
<div class="container">
<h2>What are Circadian Rhythms?</h2>
<p>Circadian rhythms are the daily timetables that are present in every cell of every organ in our body, including the brain. Circadian rhythms are the master program that instructs at what time of the day or night every brain chemical, every hormone, every enzyme rises and/or fall. These daily rhythms enable our brain and body to achieve their optimum performance at every hour of the day or night and allow our body to carry out its daily repair and rejuvenation. When we have broken circadian rhythms, the risk for many diseases including obesity, diabetes, heart disease, fatty liver disease, gut diseases, and cancer goes up. By nurturing our rhythms we can prevent, manage, and even reverse many of these diseases.</p>
</div>
</section>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec text-center">
<div class="container">
<h2>How to nurture your rhythms?</h2>
<p>When we eat, sleep and exercise shapes our rhythms. By timing these daily habits to the right time of our daily lives, we can have healthy rhythms. In this research study, we want to know how your daily habits of eating, sleeping and exercising affects your health, Based on that, we will guide you to optimize these habits which in turn will optimize your rhythms so you can lead a long, healthy life.</p>
</div>
</section>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec cnt_with_side_img rt_img">
<div class="container">
<div class="row">
<div class="col-md-6">
<article>
<h2>Track everything you
eat and drink </h2>
<p>Food, beverages, and medications can influence your body&rsquo;s circadian rhythms. Use the mCC app to log everything that you eat or drink to help us understand how the timing of food, beverages, and medication influences your circadian rhythms.</p>
</article>
</div>
<div class="col-md-6">
<figure>
<img src="https://stag.mycircadianclock.andolasoft.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/landing-food-1.png" alt="">
</figure>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</section>

</figure>
</div>
<div class="col-md-6">
<article>
<h2>Track your Exercise and Steps</h2>
<p>Use the mCC app to log your exercise and sync the mCC app with Google Fit or Apple Health to capture your daily step counts.
</p>
</article>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec much_more_sec">
<div class="container">
<div class="row">
<div class="col-md-6">
<figure>
<img src="https://stag.mycircadianclock.andolasoft.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/much-more.png" alt="">
</figure>
</div>
<div class="col-md-6">
<article>
<h2 class="much_more_ttl">And much more&hellip;</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<strong>Medicine Reminder</strong>
<p>Timing of medicines and supplements matters. By sharing what medication and when you take them will help us gain better insight into optimal timing for meds and supplements. Along the way, set reminders so that you don&rsquo;t miss your supplements and meds.</p>
</li>
<li>
<strong>Water Reminder</strong>
<p>Hydration is an energy booster. If you often forget to hydrate enough, use the app to track your intake and stay hydrated.</p>
</li>
<li>
<strong>Health Log</strong>
<p>You can help our research on how the timing of food, sleep and exercise affects your health by periodically sharing your health measurements. They include body weight, blood pressure, blood glucose and a few more.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</article>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec text-center">
<div class="container">
<h2>What are Circadian Rhythms?</h2>
<p>Circadian rhythms are the daily timetables that are present in every cell of every organ in our body, including the brain. Circadian rhythms are the master program that instructs at what time of the day or night every brain chemical, every hormone, every enzyme rises and/or fall. These daily rhythms enable our brain and body to achieve their optimum performance at every hour of the day or night and allow our body to carry out its daily repair and rejuvenation. When we have broken circadian rhythms, the risk for many diseases including obesity, diabetes, heart disease, fatty liver disease, gut diseases, and cancer goes up. By nurturing our rhythms we can prevent, manage, and even reverse many of these diseases.</p>
</div>
</section>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec text-center">
<div class="container">
<h2>How to nurture your rhythms?</h2>
<p>When we eat, sleep and exercise shapes our rhythms. By timing these daily habits to the right time of our daily lives, we can have healthy rhythms. In this research study, we want to know how your daily habits of eating, sleeping and exercising affects your health, Based on that, we will guide you to optimize these habits which in turn will optimize your rhythms so you can lead a long, healthy life.</p>
</div>
</section>

 X-Content-Type-Options Header Missing
Description
The Anti-MIME-Sniffing header X-Content-Type-Options was not set to 'nosniff'. This allows older versions of Internet Explorer and Chrome to perform MIME-sniffing on the response body, potentially causing the response body to be interpreted and displayed as a content type other than the declared content type. Current (early 2014) and legacy versions of Firefox will use the declared content type (if one is set), rather than performing MIME-sniffing.

Method GET
Parameter x-content-type-options
Attack
Evidence
Other Info This issue still applies to error type pages (401, 403, 500, etc.) as those pages are often still affected by injection issues, in which case there is still concern for browsers sniffing pages away from their actual content type. At "High" threshold this scan rule will not alert on client or server error responses.

</figure>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec text-center">
<div class="container">
<h2>What are Circadian Rhythms?</h2>
<p>Circadian rhythms are the daily timetables that are present in every cell of every organ in our body, including the brain. Circadian rhythms are the master program that instructs at what time of the day or night every brain chemical, every hormone, every enzyme rises and/or fall. These daily rhythms enable our brain and body to achieve their optimum performance at every hour of the day or night and allow our body to carry out its daily repair and rejuvenation. When we have broken circadian rhythms, the risk for many diseases including obesity, diabetes, heart disease, fatty liver disease, gut diseases, and cancer goes up. By nurturing our rhythms we can prevent, manage, and even reverse many of these diseases.</p>
</div>
</section>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec text-center">
<div class="container">
<h2>How to nurture your rhythms?</h2>
<p>When we eat, sleep and exercise shapes our rhythms. By timing these daily habits to the right time of our daily lives, we can have healthy rhythms. In this research study, we want to know how your daily habits of eating, sleeping and exercising affects your health, Based on that, we will guide you to optimize these habits which in turn will optimize your rhythms so you can lead a long, healthy life.</p>
</div>
</section>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec cnt_with_side_img rt_img">
<div class="container">
<div class="row">
<div class="col-md-6">
<article>
<h2>Track everything you
eat and drink </h2>
<p>Food, beverages, and medications can influence your body&rsquo;s circadian rhythms. Use the mCC app to log everything that you eat or drink to help us understand how the timing of food, beverages, and medication influences your circadian rhythms.</p>
</article>
</div>
<div class="col-md-6">
<figure>
<img src="https://stag.mycircadianclock.andolasoft.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/landing-food-1.png" alt="">
</figure>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</section>

</figure>

<div class="col-md-6">
<article>
<h2>Track your Exercise and Steps</h2>
<p>Use the mCC app to log your exercise and sync the mCC app with Google Fit or Apple Health to capture your daily step counts.
</p>
</article>

<section class="cmn_cnt_sec much_more_sec">
<div class="container">
<div class="row">
<div class="col-md-6">
<figure>

</figure>
</div>
<div class="col-md-6">
<article>
<h2 class="much_more_ttl">And much more&hellip;</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<strong>Medicine Reminder</strong>
<p>Timing of medicines and supplements matters. By sharing what medication and when you take them will help us gain better insight into optimal timing for meds and supplements. Along the way, set reminders so that you don&rsquo;t miss your supplements and meds.</p>
</li>
<li>
<strong>Water Reminder</strong>
<p>Hydration is an energy booster. If you often forget to hydrate enough, use the app to track your intake and stay hydrated.</p>
</li>
<li>
<strong>Health Log</strong>
<p>You can help our research on how the timing of food, sleep and exercise affects your health by periodically sharing your health measurements. They include body weight, blood pressure, blood glucose and a few more.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</article>

function setCurrentTheme( theme ) {
var pictures = document.getElementsByClassName( 'neve-site-logo' );
for(var i = 0; i<pictures.length; i++) {
var picture = pictures.item(i);
if( ! picture ) {
continue;
};
var fileExt = picture.src.slice((Math.max(0, picture.src.lastIndexOf(".")) || Infinity) + 1);
if ( fileExt === 'svg' ) {
picture.removeAttribute('width');
picture.removeAttribute('height');
picture.style = 'width: var(--maxwidth)';
}
var compId = picture.getAttribute('data-variant');
if ( compId && variants[compId] ) {
var isConditional = variants[compId]['same'];
if ( theme === 'light' || isConditional || variants[compId]['dark']['src'] === false ) {
picture.src = variants[compId]['light']['src'];
picture.srcset = variants[compId]['light']['srcset'] || '';
picture.sizes = variants[compId]['light']['sizes'];
continue;
};
picture.src = variants[compId]['dark']['src'];
picture.srcset = variants[compId]['dark']['srcset'] || '';
picture.sizes = variants[compId]['dark']['sizes'];
};
};
};
var observer = new MutationObserver(function(mutations) {
mutations.forEach(function(mutation) {
if (mutation.type == 'attributes') {
theme = html.getAttribute('data-neve-theme');
setCurrentTheme(theme);
};
});
});
observer.observe(html, {
attributes: true
});

:where(.is-position-sticky){--wp-admin--admin-bar--position-offset:var(--wp-admin--admin-bar--height,0px)}@media screen and (max-width:600px){html :where(.is-position-sticky){--wp-admin--admin-bar--position-offset:0px}}
Instances 3
Solution
Ensure that the application/web server sets the Content-Type header appropriately, and that it sets the X-Content-Type-Options header to 'nosniff' for all web pages.

If possible, ensure that the end user uses a standards-compliant and modern web browser that does not perform MIME-sniffing at all, or that can be directed by the web application/web server to not perform MIME-sniffing.
Reference https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/previous-versions/windows/internet-explorer/ie-developer/compatibility/gg622941(v=vs.85)
https://owasp.org/www-community/Security_Headers
